From Robert Andrew Ryan Subject Re Monthly Question about XCopyArea and Expose Events Excerpts from Apr Monthly Question about Buzz M A button widget when pressed will cause a new item to be drawn in the This action clearly should not call XCopyArea or equiv directly instead it should register the existence of the new item in a memory structure and let the same expose event handler that handles regular expose events window manager driven exposures take care of rendering the new Clearly Depends on your programming It is not at all forbidden to draw outside the context of an expose Certainly any internal data structures should be maintained such that the visual appearance would be maintained properly whenever an expose event happens to be This doesn't preclude drawing immediately after updating the datastructures Rob